comments.body:
[~decker] and I reviewed the logs, and although we don't have the full picture, we believe [~decker] analysis before is accurate, with the addition that the loss of the secondary CLC, happened at a time that caused a failure to write a transaction to the DB

{code}
cloud-output.log.6:2013-02-19 09:23:54  WARN | javax.persistence.PersistenceException: unexpected error when rollbacking
cloud-output.log.6:2013-02-19 09:23:54  WARN | Failed to get property: bootstrap.webservices.channel_keep_alive because of unexpected error when rollbacking
{code}

after that the primary CLC started to drain all its connections to the the DB, till no connections were left in the pool. At that time, no transaction can be completed hence even the switch of the CC state cannot be registered:

{code}
2013-02-19 09:24:47 ERROR | ENABLE:ENABLED  arn:euca:eucalyptus:cluster01:cluster:cc01/ DISABLED->ENABLED=NOTREADY [No active databases in cluster eucalyptus_general]
2013-02-19 09:24:48 ERROR | db resource check failed for eucalyptus_config
{code}

In this situation a restart of the CLC with the problematic DB connection, should restore the service.

[~decker] mentioned that this issue has been resolved in 3.2.1. The only rollback bug I have found in 3.2.1 is euca-4721, so I will need [~decker] to confirm which one is the related issue.
